sentences: Stella Corkery (born 1960) is a New Zealand visual artist and drummer, born in Tuatapere, New Zealand.
Corkery attended the Elam School of Fine Art (University of Auckland) where she received a BFA (Hons) First Class Honors in 2012 and Master of Fine Arts (MFA) in 2013.
Corkery attended the Elam School of Fine Art (University of Auckland) where she received a BFA (Hons) First Class Honors in 2012 and Master of Fine Arts (MFA) in 2013.
Her visual works include Smoke and Butterfly (2015) and Gas Light (2015).
In 2013 Corkery was selected to be part of the exhibition Freedom Farmers: New Zealand Artists Growing Ideas at the Auckland Art Gallery Toi o Tamaki.

Corkery's recent exhibitions in New Zealand include: Necessary Distraction: a painting show (Auckland Art Gallery Toi o Tamaki, 2015, with Saskia Leek, Julian Hooper, Nicola Farquhar, Kirstin Carlin, and James Cousins); Porous Moonlight (Papakura Art Gallery, 2013); and Episodic Nomadic (Gloria Knight, Auckland, 2013).

Corkery is a self-taught drummer and has been involved in the underground music scene since the late 1980s.
She currently lives and works in Auckland, New Zealand.
In the early 1990s she started the Pink Air and Girl Alliance record labels with her partner Alan Holt.
